<p>Columbus's Cold-Mixed climate requires HVAC systems capable of handling temperature extremes from sub-freezing winters to hot, humid summers with temperatures reaching the 80s and 90s. For optimal efficiency and year-round comfort, homeowners should consider heat pump systems with SEER ratings of 16-20 and HSPF ratings of 9-10. Dual-fuel systems combining heat pumps with gas furnace backup work exceptionally well in Columbus, providing efficient cooling and heating while maintaining comfort during extreme cold snaps when heat pumps lose efficiency.</p>

