<p>Columbus residents benefit from several attractive incentives for solar and HVAC investments. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on total solar installation costs through 2032, making it an ideal time for Columbus homeowners to go solar. This credit applies to the full system cost including equipment, installation, and necessary electrical work, significantly reducing the upfront investment.</p>

<p>While Ohio doesn't offer state-level solar rebates, AEP Ohio provides energy efficiency rebates for qualifying HVAC equipment. Heat pump installations can qualify for rebates of \$300-\$800 depending on efficiency ratings, while smart thermostats may qualify for additional rebates of \$50-\$100. Columbus homeowners should also explore the Ohio Energy Loan Fund, which offers low-interest financing for energy efficiency improvements, including both solar panels and HVAC upgrades.</p>

