<p>Columbus homeowners have multiple financing options for solar and HVAC projects. Solar loans typically offer terms of 10-20 years with interest rates ranging from 3-8%, making monthly payments comparable to current AEP Ohio bills. Many installers offer zero-down financing, allowing immediate energy savings that often exceed loan payments from day one.</p>

<p>Property value increases in Columbus average 3-4% for homes with solar installations, adding approximately \$15,000-\$20,000 in value for typical systems. HVAC upgrades similarly boost home values while providing immediate comfort and efficiency benefits. The combination of energy savings, tax credits, and property value increases typically generates positive returns within 8-12 years for Columbus residents.</p>

